- To create 7zip data files to put in data use the command: '/opt/Qt/Tools/QtInstallerFramework/3.0/bin/archivegen shaco.7z ShaCo'
- Move the 7zip file in data (remove the directory with ShaCo.exe and libraries)
- To create the installer use the command: '/opt/Qt/Tools/QtInstallerFramework/3.0/bin/binarycreator -c config/config.xml -p packages PolyShaper'

- On windows, to collect all files necessary for installation
    - copy ShaCo.exe in an empty directory
    - run: export PATH=$PATH:/c/Qt/Tools/mingw530_32/bin/:/c/Qt/5.11.1/mingw53_32/bin/
    - run: C:/Qt/5.11.1/mingw53_32/bin/windeployqt.exe --qmldir /c/Users/tomas/Desktop/ShaCo/ShaCo/qmlgit  ShaCo.exe
    - do the steps above to create the 7zip file and the installer, BUT ALSO INCLUDE THE CONTENT OF QT qml DIRECTORY (All dirs in qml inside the same dir of ShaCo.exe,
      only non-debug libraries). Some of the dirs are perhaps useless, try to reduce the set to the bare minimum

- Possible command to install drivers:
    rundll32 newdev DiInstallDriverA NULL <path-to-inf> 0 NULL
- Useful links:
    https://social.msdn.microsoft.com/Forums/windowsdesktop/en-US/60f4b917-93c9-400a-b91a-15375a8793bf/installing-driver-using-inf-file-from-command-line-on-windows-7-64-bit-failing
    https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows-hardware/drivers/install/setupapi-functions-that-simplify-driver-installation
